article.description: Adam Grant had 21 points as Bryant rolled past Wagner 79-58 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Grant scores 21 as Bryant snaps skid, wallops Wagner 79-58
article.linkText: Grant scores 21 as Bryant snaps skid, wallops Wagner 79-58
article.story: SMITHFIELD, R.I. -- Adam Grant had 21 points as Bryant rolled past Wagner 79-58 on Thursday night. With the victory Bryant matched its win total from all of last season. Charles Pride had 16 points and eight rebounds for the Bulldogs (10-9, 2-4 Northeast Conference), who snapped a four-game losing streak. Michael Green III added 15 points. Benson Lin had 11. Elijah Ford had 19 points and seven rebounds for the Seahawks (5-13, 2-5). Curtis Cobb III added 18 points. Alex Morales, whose 14 points per game coming into the contest ranked second on the Seahawks, shot only 13 percent for the game (1 of 8). Bryant plays Mount St. Mary's on the road on Saturday. Wagner matches up against Central Connecticut on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
